Others: San Antonio Spurs lost to the OKC Thunder with a score of 105-93.
Victor Wembanyama struggled offensively, scoring 6 points with 8 rebounds and 2 assists.
Wembanyama shot 1-for-5 from the field, 0-for-3 from three-point range, and 4-for-4 from the free-throw line.
Chet Holmgren and the OKC Thunder's defense effectively kept Wembanyama out of the paint and limited his scoring opportunities.
San Antonio Spurs shot 12-for-36 from three-point range, indicating the Thunder's defensive strategy was successful.
